Task 2 – Phishing Email Investigation Report

Case Information
Case ID: PH-2026-002

Email Subject: Action Required: Password Reset Attempt

Claimed Sender: IT Support Team

Actual Sender: it-support@micros0ft-security.com

Date Received: 17 Feb 2026

Technical Email Header Investigation
Key Header Fields Examined:
Header Field	Observation	Risk
From	micros0ft-security.com	Fake domain
Reply-To	attacker123@gmail.com	Mismatch
Return-Path	randomserver.ru	Suspicious origin
SPF	Softfail	Authentication issue
DKIM	None	No signature
DMARC	Fail	Policy violation

Finding:
The email failed authentication checks (SPF, DKIM, DMARC), confirming spoofing.

Domain Intelligence Analysis
Suspicious Domain:
micros0ft-security.com

Observations:

Uses “0” instead of “o” (typosquatting)

Newly registered domain

No official Microsoft ownership

Threat Type:
Typosquatting Attack (Look-alike domain)

URL & Redirection Analysis
Displayed Text:
https://microsoft.com/reset

Actual Hyperlink:
http://micros0ft-security.com/reset-login

Uses:
HTTP (not HTTPS)
Similar-looking domain
Credential harvesting page

Attachment Risk Analysis
Attachment Name:

Password_Reset_Form.html

Risk Indicators:

HTML attachments often contain credential harvesting forms

Can redirect to phishing website

No digital signature

Behavioral & Social Engineering Analysis
The email uses:

Fear trigger → “Unauthorized login attempt detected”

Urgency → “Reset password within 30 minutes”

Authority → “Microsoft Security Department”

Scarcity → “Account will be locked permanently”

This manipulates emotional response before logical thinking.

Attack Classification
Category	Type
Attack Type	Phishing
Subtype	Credential Harvesting
Technique	Email Spoofing
Tactic	Social Engineering
Delivery	Malicious Link

Risk Impact Assessment
If user clicks:

Credentials stolen

Account takeover

Lateral movement possible

Data breach risk

Financial fraud risk

Recommended Response (Incident Handling)
Do not interact with email.

Block sender domain.

Report to SOC/IT.

Run endpoint antivirus scan.

Reset passwords (if clicked).

Enable MFA immediately.

Advanced Interview-Level Answers
️What is phishing?
Phishing is a social engineering attack where attackers impersonate trusted entities to trick users into revealing sensitive information or installing malware.

️What is email spoofing?
Email spoofing is forging the sender address in an email to make it appear as if it came from a legitimate source.

️How do attackers bypass spam filters?
Using look-alike domains

Compromised legitimate accounts

Sending low-volume targeted emails

Using URL shorteners

Embedding links inside images

️How to technically verify sender authenticity?
Check SPF, DKIM, DMARC results

Validate domain registration age

Compare return-path and reply-to

Inspect originating IP reputation

Use threat intelligence platforms

️What is typosquatting?
Registering domains similar to legitimate brands to trick users (example: micros0ft.com).
